<paragraph id="8BF18A61FFAC9E26B4CA3D55C2DFF60D" blockId="0.[151,1437,1155,1973]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B4CA3D55C15BF56C" bold="true" box="[199,316,1300,1324]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B54F3D54C276F56D" authority="Gyulai, 2019" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,529,1301,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B54F3D54C276F56D" box="[322,529,1301,1325]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Valeria wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B6153D54C233F56D" bold="true" box="[536,596,1301,1325]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209EB08FFAC9E26B6153D54C233F56D" box="[536,596,1301,1325]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="137596E4FFAC9E26B66E3D54C2C6F56D" box="[611,673,1301,1325]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1692,1714]" captionTargetBox="[159,1416,179,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,167,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Adults. 1. Valeria wassalberti sp. n., holotype, Iran, prov. Hormozgan, 80 km N. of Bandar Abbas, slide GYP 5057 (coll. P. Gyulai); 2. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Kermanshah, Zagros, slide GYP 5059 (coll. P. Gyulai)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3534838" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3534838/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) is a medium sized species, similar only to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B0933D54C17FF510" authority="(Wiltshire, 1957)" authorityName="Wiltshire" authorityYear="1957" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B0933D54C531F56D" box="[1182,1366,1301,1325]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Valeria carducha</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDFF790FFAC9E26B16E3D54C177F510" author="Wiltshire, E. P." pageId="0" pageNumber="394" refId="ref1413" refString="Wiltshire, E. P. (1957) The Lepidoptera of Iraq. Dorking, Alard and Son, London, 162 pp." type="book" year="1957">Wiltshire, 1957</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="137596E4FFAC9E26B52B3D78C10EF511" box="[294,361,1337,1361]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1692,1714]" captionTargetBox="[159,1416,179,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,167,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Adults. 1. Valeria wassalberti sp. n., holotype, Iran, prov. Hormozgan, 80 km N. of Bandar Abbas, slide GYP 5057 (coll. P. Gyulai); 2. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Kermanshah, Zagros, slide GYP 5059 (coll. P. Gyulai)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3534838" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3534838/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
; the 
<typeStatus id="54F534C3FFAC9E26B5903D78C19DF511" box="[413,506,1337,1361]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">holotype</typeStatus>
(male) and 
<typeStatus id="54F534C3FFAC9E26B6713D78C285F511" box="[636,738,1337,1361]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">paratypes</typeStatus>
are figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDFF790FFAC9E26B7853D78C498F511" author="Ronkay, G. &amp; Ronkay, L. &amp; Gyulai, P." box="[904,1279,1337,1361]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" refId="ref1298" refString="Ronkay, G., Ronkay, L. &amp; Gyulai, P. (2011) Cuculliinae II and Psaphidinae-The Witt Ctalogue. Vol. 5. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 380 pp." type="book" year="2011">Ronkay, Ronkay &amp; Gyulai (2011))</bibRefCitation>
, from which it is distinguished by the size and some of the external and genitalia features. The distinctive external key features are as follows: the new species is significantly smaller than 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B6D13DC0C33CF5D9" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[732,859,1409,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B6D13DC0C33CF5D9" box="[732,859,1409,1433]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="4CB62784FFAC9E26B7663DC0C3DCF5D8" box="[875,955,1409,1433]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" unit="mm" value="27.0">27 mm</quantity>
, versus 
<quantity id="4CB62784FFAC9E26B01E3DC0C4EEF5D8" box="[1043,1161,1409,1433]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" unit="mm" value="35.0" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="32.0">32–38 mm</quantity>
, no significant difference between the males and females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B6003DE4C2EBF5FD" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[525,652,1445,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B6003DE4C2EBF5FD" box="[525,652,1445,1469]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the ground colour of vesture of head and thorax and forewings is light greyish, versus light brownish and somewhat darker, with much stronger, darker medial fascia and postmedial line in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B1843D88C09CF645" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B1843D88C09CF645" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Hindwings of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B5A93DACC25DF645" authority="Gyulai, 2019" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[420,570,1517,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B5A93DACC25DF645" box="[420,570,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B64F3DACC218F645" bold="true" box="[578,639,1517,1541]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209EB08FFAC9E26B64F3DACC218F645" box="[578,639,1517,1541]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are also greyish, unicolorous, while more variegated, whitish with brown suffusion in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B54E3E50C1A6F669" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[323,449,1553,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B54E3E50C1A6F669" box="[323,449,1553,1577]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly on the main veins and in the margin. Cilia lighter, whitish, the discal spot in the hindwings is more conspicuous in the new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF18A61FFAC9E26B4CA3E18C405F7F5" blockId="0.[151,1437,1155,1973]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
In the female genitalia, the differences between 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B6CF3E18C331F631" authority="Gyulai, 2019" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[706,854,1625,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B6CF3E18C331F631" box="[706,854,1625,1649]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B7513E18C3F0F631" bold="true" box="[860,919,1625,1649]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209EB08FFAC9E26B7513E18C3F0F631" box="[860,919,1625,1649]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="137596E4FFAC9E26B7A83E18C384F631" box="[933,995,1625,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1764,1786]" captionTargetBox="[159,1416,179,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,167,1672]" captionText="FIGURES 3–5. Female genitalia. 3. Valeria wassalberti sp. n., holotype, Iran, prov. Hormozgan, 80 km N. of Bandar Abbas, slide GYP 5057 (coll. P. Gyulai); 4. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Kermanshah, Zagros, slide GYP 5059 (coll. P. Gyulai); 5. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Khorassan, Kopeth Dagh, slide GYP 5058 (coll. P. Gyulai)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613672/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B0123E18C4C7F631" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[1055,1184,1625,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B0123E18C4C7F631" box="[1055,1184,1625,1649]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="137596E4FFAC9E26B0A03E18C56CF630" box="[1197,1291,1624,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1764,1786]" captionTargetBox="[159,1416,179,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,167,1672]" captionText="FIGURES 3–5. Female genitalia. 3. Valeria wassalberti sp. n., holotype, Iran, prov. Hormozgan, 80 km N. of Bandar Abbas, slide GYP 5057 (coll. P. Gyulai); 4. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Kermanshah, Zagros, slide GYP 5059 (coll. P. Gyulai); 5. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Khorassan, Kopeth Dagh, slide GYP 5058 (coll. P. Gyulai)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613672/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
; one from SE 
<collectingCountry id="F359CAF1FFAC9E26B49A3E3CC0A5F6D4" box="[151,194,1661,1684]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
and one from NE 
<collectingCountry id="F359CAF1FFAC9E26B5853E3CC1D0F6D5" box="[392,439,1661,1685]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
), are found in the shape, size and sclerotization of the antrum–ostium complex, ductus bursae and appendix bursae. The new species has calycular, less sclerotized antrum–ostium complex with V–shaped medial incision of the dorsal plate of ostium, while those are more sclerotized, broader with more or less broadly U–shaped ostium plate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B4E33EA8C135F741" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[238,338,1769,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B4E33EA8C135F741" box="[238,338,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B5713EA8C276F741" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[380,529,1769,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B5713EA8C276F741" box="[380,529,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ductus bursae is much narrower (particularly its posterior part tube–like and not sclerotized); whereas it is much broader, anterior section is more sclerotized, wrinkled, posterior section evenly dilated but shorter in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B55F3F70C1D1F709" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[338,438,1841,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B55F3F70C1D1F709" box="[338,438,1841,1865]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in the new species, the appendix bursae is larger and more prominent. The correct separation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B4B83F14C12DF72D" authority="Gyulai, 2019" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[181,330,1877,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B4B83F14C12DF72D" box="[181,330,1877,1901]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209EB08FFAC9E26B55F3F14C1E8F72C" box="[338,399,1877,1901]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B55F3F14C1EFF72D" bold="true" box="[338,392,1877,1901]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B5CE3F14C21BF72D" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[451,636,1877,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B5CE3F14C21BF72D" box="[451,636,1877,1901]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Valeria carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is supported by the allopatric distribution of the two species; the new species is known only from the southernmost 
<collectingCountry id="F359CAF1FFAC9E26B6543F38C2E0F7D0" box="[601,647,1913,1936]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
, not very far from the Persian Gulf, whereas the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EF1E2FFAC9E26B0853F38C558F7D1" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[1160,1343,1913,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis id="B93A5673FFAC9E26B0853F38C558F7D1" box="[1160,1343,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Valeria carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not so local, occurs both in 
<collectingCountry id="F359CAF1FFAC9E26B57B3FDCC1C6F7F4" box="[374,417,1949,1972]" name="Iraq" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iraq</collectingCountry>
(eastern parts) and 
<collectingCountry id="F359CAF1FFAC9E26B67E3FDCC2F9F7F4" box="[627,670,1949,1972]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
(from the NW and SW to the NE of 
<collectingCountry id="F359CAF1FFAC9E26B02A3FDCC431F7F5" box="[1063,1110,1949,1973]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
